-films-win-in-madrid | title = Two PH Films Win in Madrid | work = Indie Bravo | publisher = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] | date = 26 July 2016 | accessdate = 4 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Tomodachi 2\">{{cite web | url = http://www.pep.ph/guide/movies/24036/emtomodachiem-starring-jacky-woo-and-bela-padilla-wins-in-2016-madrid-film-fest | title = Tomodachi, Starring Jacky Woo and Bela Padilla Wins in 2016 Madrid Film Fest | author = Mendoza, Ruel | date = 11 July 2016 | accessdate = 4 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Madrid IFF 2016 Winners\">{{cite web | url = http://filmfestinternational.com/madrid-iff-2016-full-winners-list/ | title = Madrid IFF 2016 Full Winners List | publisher = Film Fest International | accessdate = 4 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Felix Manalo\">{{cite web | url = http://felixmanalothemovie.com/index.php/about-the-film | website = FelixManaloTheMovie.com | title = About the Film | publisher = Viva Films | accessdate = 19 May 2017 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150920002957/http://www.felixmanalothemovie.com/index.php/about-the-film | archive-date = 20 September 2015 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Heartbreak\">{{cite news | url = http://www.manilatimes.net/a-dramedy-to-empower-heartbroken-women/281605/ | title = A dramedy to empower brokenhearted women | author = Alpad, Christina | date = 23 August 2016 | newspaper = Manila Times | accessdate = 19 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Girl Robin\">{{cite web | url = http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/302023/showbiz/bela-padilla-about-her-role-on-love-and-lies-i-get-to-be-the-girl-robin-padilla-in-this-show|title=Bela Padilla about her role on Love and Lies: 'I get to be the girl Robin Padilla in this show'|author=|date=|work=gmanetwork.com|accessdate=23 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Bela's Second Fiddle\">{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/88751/bela-padilla-doesnt-mind-being-second-fiddle|title=Bela Padilla doesn\u2019t mind being second 